verbose_text: Therefore, the phages were heated to either 60degreesC (low stringency) or 80degreesC (high stringency) before panning, which resulted in 4 different groups : S60 (phage produced without FkpA over-expression and heated to 60degreesC), S80 (phage produced without FkpA over-expression and heated to 80degreesC), F60 (phage produced with FkpA over-expression and heated to 60degreesC), and F80 (phage produced with FkpA over-expression and heated to 80degreesC).
